NoBroker is a [[Bangalore]] based real estate search portal that connects flat owners and tenants directly with each other.<ref name="techinasia.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/engineers-harassed-real-estate-brokers-started-nobroker/|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|publisher=}}</ref><ref name="e27.co">{{cite web|url=http://e27.co/need-nobroker-find-dream-house-20150720/|title=Why you need NoBroker to find your dream house|work=e27}}</ref> The company does not charge any brokerage from either parties but they have some service packages range from worth 999 to 5,999. <ref>[http://{{cite%20web|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/magazine/features/taking-you-home/story/257816.html]</ref> <ref name="indiatimes.com">{{cite web|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/absence-of-organised-players-in-the-house-rental-space-gives-newbies-like-nobroker-grabhouse-others-a-perfect-space/articleshow/47684011.cms|title=Absence of organised players in the house rental space gives newbies like NoBroker, Grabhouse, others a perfect space|work=The Economic Times}}</ref> Founded in 2014, the company has 4 lac users, which it claims are genuine owners and home seekers. It is operational in 5 cities namely, Mumbai, Bangalore, Pune, Chennai and Gurugram<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/startup/nobrokercom-to-expand-to-5-more-cities-this-year-1015329.html|title=NoBroker.com to expand to 5 more cities this year}}</ref>.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/checkin/nobroker.com-ventures-into-property-resale/41409/1|title=NoBroker.com ventures into property resale {{!}} Forbes India|website=Forbes India|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-06}}</ref><ref name="sriramsharma">{{cite web|url=http://gadgets.ndtv.com/internet/features/seven-startups-thatll-help-you-find-a-house-without-a-broker-758191|title=Seven Startups That'll Help You Find a House, Without a Broker|author=Sriram Sharma|work=NDTV Gadgets360.com}}</ref>

NoBroker was founded by IIT and [[IIM Ahmedabad]] graduates, Amit Kumar Agarwal, Akhil Gupta & Saurabh Garg because they claimed that brokers do not add value in the real estate transaction and still charge heavy brokerage.<ref name="techinasia.com"/><ref name="e27.co"/><ref name="sriramsharma"/> NoBroker claims to work on the backbone of a [[technology]] that identifies and bans brokers. Early 2014 NoBroker started operations in Mumbai.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/engineers-harassed-real-estate-brokers-started-nobroker|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|publisher=}}</ref> As on date NoBroker has operations in Mumbai, Bangalore, Pune, Chennai and Gurugram.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/Realty-portal-NoBroker-enters-Chennai/articleshow/47429140.cms|title=Realty portal NoBroker enters Chennai|work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Companies/7YYbaHz6pTwlEwPTVV5C7M/NoBroker-to-expand-to-20-cities-in-six-months-to-boost-suppl.html|title=NoBroker to expand to 20 cities in six months to boost supply|first=|date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=|author=Mihir Dalal|work=Live Mint}}</ref>

In February 2014, the company raised $3M in series A from [[SAIF Partners]] and Fulcrum Venture India,  venture capital companies in India.<ref name="indiatimes.com"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2015/02/22/nobroker/|title=Peer-To-Peer Rental Service NoBroker Grabs $3M To Battle India’s Property Brokers|date=22 February 2015|publisher=AOL|work=TechCrunch}}</ref> NoBroker had started as a rental platform but it recently forayed into brokerage free buy/sell property as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://forbesindia.com/article/checkin/nobroker.com-ventures-into-property-resale/41409/1|title=Forbes India Magazine - NoBroker.com ventures into property resale|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/wealth/real-estate/news/property-listing-site-nobroker-enters-re-sale-market/articleshow/49276784.cms|title=Property listing site NoBroker enters re-sale market|work=The Economic Times}}</ref> In February 2016 NoBroker has closed series B funding of $10M from Japan-based BeeNext.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/02/24/nobroker-10-million-series-b/|title=India’s NoBroker Lands $10M To Make Property Agents Obsolete|date=24 February 2016|publisher=AOL|work=TechCrunch}}</ref>

NoBroker created an algorithm which identifies and bans brokers from the portal.<ref name="technotreats.com">{{cite web|url=https://technotreats.com/2015/07/11/nobroker/|title=No Broker website and app to rent houses more easily|work=TechnoTreats}}</ref> They offer services like creating and registering [[rental agreement]]s and getting it home delivered.<ref name="technotreats.com"/>
The company is operated on both app and web.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Companies/h1hr95FyRWdKdTLcnUPCJN/NoBroker-launches-mobile-app.html|title=NoBroker launches mobile app|first=|date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=|author=Mihir Dalal|work=Live Mint}}</ref>

According to some media reports the company’s office in Bangalore was attacked by local brokers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Companies/L4O6Z8weBdn38y5oEtciYI/NoBroker-office-attacked-in-Bengaluru.html|title=NoBroker office attacked in Bengaluru|first=|date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=|author=Mihir Dalal|work=Live Mint}}</ref>

