{{Infobox Magazine| |title =The Improper Bostonian |image_file =Improper_mag.gif | image_size = | image_caption = ''The Improper Bostonian''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s (February 20, 2008) – (March 3, 2008) cover | editor = Matt Martinelli | editor_title = Editor | frequency = Bi-weekly | category = Regional| | company = Improper Publications, Inc. | founded = 1991 | total_circulation = 91,934<ref>"[http://abcas3.accessabc.com/ecirc/magform.asp eCirc for Consumer Magazines]". ''[[Audit Bureau of Circulations (North America)|Audit Bureau of Circulations]]''. Retrieved November 1, 2011.</ref> | circulation_year = 2011 | firstdate = | country = [[United States]] | based = [[Boston]] | language = [[English language|English]] | website = [http://www.improper.com The Improper Bostonian] | issn = }}
'''''The Improper Bostonian''''' is a glossy lifestyle guide for the city of [[Boston]]. The magazine comes out bi-weekly and reports on the area trends in a young and entertaining way. The magazine is a staple of the city, being free to people inside the city, and $29.95 a year<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.improper.com/magazine/|title=Subscriptions|accessdate=4 November 2017}}</ref> for people who live outside Boston. The magazine covers music, theater, sports, fashion, personals, shopping and local events.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.improper.com/index.html|title=The Improper Bostonian|accessdate=February 29, 2008|work=Improper Bostonian|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070911233557/http://www.improper.com/index.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate=September 11, 2007}}</ref>
The magazine also holds or sponsors events in the city ranging from balls to events benefiting the homeless and children.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.improper.com/events.html |title=Improper Events|accessdate=February 29, 2008|work=Improper Bostonian}}</ref>
When it was first published, it was a newsprint tabloid and over time it has changed format, upgrading several times. ''The Improper Bostonian'' was founded by Mark Semonian in 1991. His sister, Wendy, is currently the publisher. The publication has belonged to the family of its publisher since its inception.
